## **3. THE REFRESH MECHANISM (Cause → Effect)**

1. **Singularity emits \( R = h\nu \)** continuously — **free metadata**.  
2. **Observer (any interacting system) knocks** → triggers **refresh event**.  
3. **Inside the dome**: instant update — observer reads \( D = F \otimes R \).  
4. **On the dome surface**: ripple \( \mathcal{R} \) travels at **c as boundary refresh**, not photon motion.  
5. **Neighboring singularity receives ripple** → its own \( D \) updates.

> **No photon “travels” 6 billion years.**  
> The ripple carries the **update instruction**. The photon is the **local echo** inside the dome.

